A sightseeing boat with 26 people aboard was flooded and sunk off the coast of the Shiretoko Peninsula in Japan's Hokkaido on Saturday. The Japan Coast Guard (JCG), which received the report at around 1:15 p.m. local time (0415GMT), said it had not found the boat "KAZU I" nor the people on board as of 8 p.m., adding that their fate remains unknown, Kyodo News reported. Twenty-four passengers including two children are aboard the boat along with two crew members, the JCG said, adding it was searching the sea area around the site by sending patrol boats and helicopters. The boat reported to its operator that it was tilting 30 degrees around 3 p.m. before losing contact, according to the JCG. (Cover: The Shiretoko Peninsula of Hokkaido, Japan, September 25, 2021. /CFP)